== Mash ==

Boil a full #kettle{} of water.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the pan and cook until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-18%minutes}.

== Chicken and Mushrooms ==

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{}
on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}
to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{1} (use #scissors{} if easier).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Sauce ==

Once the chicken and mushrooms are cooked through, add the garlic to the pan.
Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce, then
bring to the boil and reduce by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @wholegrain mustard{17%g} until
everything's piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Finishing the Mash ==

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to
the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} along with half the
chives. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, spoon the mash into your #bowls{}.

Share out the creamy mustard chicken.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining chives over the top. Enjoy!